## Phase 4.1.5 - Control selection observability and advisory gates (tertiary)

This node extends 4.1.4 by making control-selection evidence observable and audit-ready while keeping all execution closure claims explicitly deferred.

### Objectives

- Define a deterministic observability envelope for control-selection outcomes and drift signals.
- Keep replay-literal and CI closure work advisory-open for execution track handling.
- Preserve `@skipUntil(D-032)` and avoid closure inflation in conceptual mapping.

### Contract sketch

| Step | Input | Output | Constraint |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Record selection witness | `SelectedGoldenRows_v0`, `tick_key` | `SelectionWitnessEnvelope_v0` | Read-only witness, no mutation side effects |
| Compute advisory gates | `SelectionWitnessEnvelope_v0`, `gate_policy` | `SelectionGateAdvisory_v0` | Advisory only; no PASS claim mutation |
| Emit operator-facing digest | `SelectionGateAdvisory_v0` | `ControlSelectionDigest_v0` | Explicit HOLD/OPEN semantics, no closure inflation |

### Acceptance checklist (conceptual)

- [x] Witness envelope and advisory gate outputs are explicitly read-only.
- [x] HOLD/OPEN semantics are described without CI closure claims.
- [x] Execution-deferred boundaries are explicit (`D-032`, `D-043`, REGISTRY-CI hold).
- [ ] Replay literal-field freeze and canonical hash registry remain intentionally deferred.

